A '''stratotype''' or '''type section''' is a [[Geology|geological]] term that names the [[Location (geography)|physical location]] or [[outcrop]] of a particular reference exposure of a [[Stratigraphy|stratigraphic sequence]] or stratigraphic boundary. If the stratigraphic unit is layered, it is called a stratotype, whereas the standard of reference for unlayered rocks is the [[Type locality (geology)|type locality]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://stratigraphy.org/upload/bak/strats.htm |title=Stratotypes and Type Localities |publisher=International Commission on Stratigraphy |accessdate=20 August 2017}}</ref> 

